        "text": "Alice Miller ([[Alice Miller (psychologist)]]) claims that \"many people suffer all their lives from this oppressive feeling of guilt, the sense of not having lived up to their parents' expectations....no argument can overcome these guilt feelings, for they have their beginnings in life's earliest period, and from that they derive their intensity.\" This may be linked to what Les Parrott has called \"the disease of false guilt....At the root of false guilt is the idea that what you ''feel'' must be true.\" If you ''feel'' guilty, you must ''be'' guilty!"
